OL,5,CMarathon
OL,7,FAccording to the organisation, they
OL,8,Fare not "anti-alcohol" but work to
OL,9,Fpromote "alcohol change."
OL,11,FA spokesperson said: "We are for a
OL,12,Ffuture in which people drink as a
OL,13,Fconscious choice, not a default; where
OL,14,Fthe issues which lead to alcohol
OL,15,Fproblems like poverty, mental health
OL,16,Fissues, homelessness are addressed;
OL,17,Fwhere those of us who drink too much,
OL,18,Fand our loved ones, have access to
OL,19,Fhigh-quality support whenever we need
OL,20,Fit, without shame or stigma."
